IMPORTANT: Generate a Node-RED flow JSON array for the community engine benchmark feature. The flow MUST have exactly these nodes:
1. tab node: {id, type:'tab', label:'Community Engine Benchmark'}
2. inject node: triggers every 600 seconds (repeat:'600'), once:false
3. function node: sets msg.payload = {anon_token: msg.payload.anon_token, engine_make: msg.payload.engine_make, engine_model: msg.payload.engine_model, rpm: msg.payload.rpm, coolant_temp_c: msg.payload.coolant_temp_c, fuel_burn_lph: msg.payload.fuel_burn_lph, firmware_version: 'v0.9.2'}
4. http request node: method:'POST', url:'https://atmyboat.com/api/community/benchmark', ret:'obj'
Each node needs: id (8-char hex like 'a1b2c3d4'), type, name, z (tab id), wires. Return ONLY the JSON array.

IMPORTANT: Generate a Node-RED flow JSON array for the community boat map feature. The flow MUST have exactly these nodes:
1. tab node: {id, type:'tab', label:'Community Boat Map'}
2. inject node: triggers every 3600 seconds (repeat:'3600'), once:false
3. function node: sets msg.payload = {anon_token: msg.payload.anon_token, lat_approx: Math.round(msg.payload.lat * 100)/100, lon_approx: Math.round(msg.payload.lon * 100)/100, firmware_version: 'v0.9.2', timestamp: new Date().toISOString()}
4. http request node: method:'POST', url:'https://atmyboat.com/api/community/position', ret:'obj'
Each node needs: id (8-char hex like 'a1b2c3d4'), type, name, z (tab id), wires. Return ONLY the JSON array.
